    <div class="container">
        
        <section id="ahmedabad" class="city-section">
            <h2>Ahmedabad</h2>
            <p>Ahmedabad is a major economic and industrial hub in Gujarat, India. It's known for its textile industry, educational institutions like IIM-A, and its rich historical connection to Mahatma Gandhi.</p>
            
            <h3>Key Facts</h3>
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Gujarat, India</p>
            <p><strong>Population:</strong> Approx. 8.6 million</p>
            <h3>Landmarks</h3>
            <ul class="landmarks-list">
                <li><strong>Sabarmati Ashram:</strong> The former residence of Mahatma Gandhi.</li>
                <li><strong>Adalaj Stepwell:</strong> A stunning example of Indo-Islamic architecture.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="jamnagar" class="city-section">
            <h2>Jamnagar</h2>
            <p>Jamnagar, also known as the 'Oil City of India,' is a major hub for oil and brass industries. It is also famous for its historical palaces and temples.</p>
            
            <h3>Key Facts</h3>
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Gujarat, India</p>
            <p><strong>Population:</strong> Approx. 600,000</p>
            <h3>Landmarks</h3>
            <ul class="landmarks-list">
                <li><strong>Lakhota Lake & Palace:</strong> A beautiful lake with a palace in the center.</li>
                <li><strong>Dwarkadhish Temple:</strong> A major Hindu pilgrimage site.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="junagadh" class="city-section">
            <h2>Junagadh</h2>
            <p>Junagadh is a historic city in Gujarat, nestled at the foot of the Girnar hills. It's known for its ancient forts, temples, and being a gateway to the Gir National Park, home to Asiatic lions.</p>
            
            <h3>Key Facts</h3>
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Gujarat, India</p>
            <p><strong>Population:</strong> Approx. 400,000</p>
            <h3>Landmarks</h3>
            <ul class="landmarks-list">
                <li><strong>Uparkot Fort:</strong> An ancient fort with historical caves.</li>
                <li><strong>Girnar Hills:</strong> A holy mountain range with temples of various religions.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="gandhinagar" class="city-section">
            <h2>Gandhinagar</h2>
            <p>Gandhinagar is the capital of Gujarat and is known for being one of the greenest cities in India. The city is well-planned and home to major government buildings and spiritual centers.</p>
            
            <h3>Key Facts</h3>
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Gujarat, India</p>
            <p><strong>Population:</strong> Approx. 350,000</p>
            <h3>Landmarks</h3>
            <ul class="landmarks-list">
                <li><strong>Akshardham Temple:</strong> A magnificent temple complex.</li>
                <li><strong>Indroda Nature Park:</strong> Known as 'India's Jurassic Park.'</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="pune" class="city-section">
            <h2>Pune</h2>
            <p>Pune is a major metropolitan city in Maharashtra, often referred to as the 'Oxford of the East' due to its numerous educational institutions. It's a key hub for the IT and automobile industries.</p>
            
            <h3>Key Facts</h3>
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Maharashtra, India</p>
            <p><strong>Population:</strong> Approx. 7.5 million</p>
            <h3>Landmarks</h3>
            <ul class="landmarks-list">
                <li><strong>Shaniwar Wada:</strong> An 18th-century fort with significant historical importance.</li>
                <li><strong>Aga Khan Palace:</strong> A palace where Mahatma Gandhi was imprisoned.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="haridwar" class="city-section">
            <h2>Haridwar</h2>
            <p>Haridwar is a holy city and a major pilgrimage site in Uttarakhand. Located on the banks of the River Ganga, it is famous for its temples and the evening Ganga Aarti ceremony at Har Ki Pauri.</p>
            
            <h3>Key Facts</h3>
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Uttarakhand, India</p>
            <p><strong>Population:</strong> Approx. 230,000</p>
            <h3>Landmarks</h3>
            <ul class="landmarks-list">
                <li><strong>Har Ki Pauri:</strong> The most sacred ghat for bathing in the Ganga.</li>
                <li><strong>Mansa Devi Temple:</strong> A hilltop temple accessible by a ropeway.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="mathura" class="city-section">
            <h2>Mathura</h2>
            <p>Mathura is an ancient city in Uttar Pradesh, revered as the birthplace of Lord Krishna. It is a major Hindu pilgrimage destination with countless temples and sacred ghats along the Yamuna river.</p>
            
            <h3>Key Facts</h3>
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Uttar Pradesh, India</p>
            <p><strong>Population:</strong> Approx. 450,000</p>
            <h3>Landmarks</h3>
            <ul class="landmarks-list">
                <li><strong>Krishna Janmabhoomi Temple:</strong> A temple built around the prison cell where Krishna was born.</li>
                <li><strong>Dwarkadhish Temple:</strong> A popular and beautifully carved temple.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

    </div>

